<item>
            <title>[SPARK-49688] Data races detected by SparkConnectServiceSuite over ExecuteHolder</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-49688</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;1. Test issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/longvu-db/spark/actions/runs/10903815379/job/30258793280&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/longvu-db/spark/actions/runs/10903815379/job/30258793280&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. Real issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;org.scalatest.exceptions.TestFailedDueToTimeoutException: The code passed to eventually never returned normally. Attempted 654 times over 10.001713506999998 seconds. Last failure message: Canceled did not equal Closed Execution has not been completed in Timeout(Span(10, Seconds)).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Data race among ExecuteThreadRunner, and interrupt.&lt;br/&gt;
1. Thread 1 starts an ExecuteHolder.&lt;br/&gt;
2. Thread 2 interrupts the ExecuteHolder, before 1 is completed.&lt;br/&gt;
3. The ExecuteHolder never reaches &apos;closed&apos;.&lt;br/&gt;
=&amp;gt; Confirmed, reproduced.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
